jectives. Alliances are ecosystems of exchange rather than mere tools of external balancing, the book argues, and institutional perspectives can offer an unprecedented insight into how structured cooperation can promote policy convergence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDeterrence (Strategy). 0aNuclear weaponszUnited States. 4aPolitical Studies 2022. 7aHISTORY / Military / Nuclear Warfare.2bisacsh  aAustralia.  aJapan.  aNATO.  aSouth Korea.  aUnited States.  aalliances.  adeterrence.  ainstitutions.  anuclear weapons.  arealism.1 aFrühling, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO&apos;Neil, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO'Neil, Andrew, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615073840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526150738423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526150738/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles